AGI -&nbsp;The gip of Genoa has set for next Friday, 10 May, the question > of the president of the Region, Liguria Giovanni Toti, under house arrest. The entrepreneur of the logistics Aldo Spinelli and the head of cabinet of Toti, Matteo Cozzani, will be, instead, questioned Saturday.&nbsp; The <a href="https://www.agi.it/politica/news/2024-05-07/toti-governor-liguria-corrution-26307318/"> arrest by Giovanni Toti for corruption</a>> > p.omba on the political debate a month from the vote for Europeans. And in the hive of the majority we rely on the principles of guarantee, while more than one voice arises, starting from the Minister of Justice, Carlo Nordio>, to raise doubts about the timing of measures. Location, that of the Guardasigilli, strongly criticized, on the opposite front, from Pd, M5s and Alleanza verde and left>, who strongly ask that the president of the Liguria Region dimetta immediately. Line not shared, instead, between the oppositions, from Italy alive and Action>.
<h2> The "perplexity" of Nordio</h2>
"I do not know the acts and as a guaranteeer I always think of the presumption of innocence. It seems to me that it is a matter of facts that date back to a few years ago and that the investigation was not born today but time back," says Nordio. "I exercised 40 years as a prosecutor and rarely asked for precautionary measures after years of investigation. My perplexity is never the moment when the precaution is taken against the impending election," he explains, but "if I have technical perplexities, it concerns a measure of the time when the crime was committed and the investigation began." Even if he asks whether it is "justice to watchmaking", the minister answers: "I do not like phrases made or common to hear, I prefer to keep in mind the principle of presumption of innocence."
&nbsp;
"I am a guarantee, for me a person is guilty only when he is sentenced to third degree of judgment," comments the national secretary of Forza Italia Antonio Tajani>, who in a note proclaims "the extraneity" of FI and announces the suspension of members Maurizio and Arturo Testa, involved in the investigation and the domiciles because accused of electoral corruption, aggravated by the purpose of facilitating Cosa Nostra".
&nbsp;
As for Fratelli d'Italia>, the line is expressed by the group leader in the Chamber Tommaso Foti, which at the end of the day assures "maximum attention to the facts of the Liguria Region, like the one lent for the facts of Bari and in general of Puglia", which involved the centerleft. "We hope that the investigations will be rapid and that there will be full clarity on the facts, which are the subject of the measures of the judicial authority today, and we trust that everyone will act in maximum transparency," Foti points out. While the League line is scanned by the deputy minister at Mit, Ligurian Edward Rix>i, who merely expresses "support and firm solidarity" at Toti.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
